#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:11
msgid ""
"Identifier-locator addressing (ILA) is a technique used with IPv6 that "
"differentiates between location and identity of a network node. Part of an "
"address expresses the immutable identity of the node, and another part "
"indicates the location of the node which can be dynamic. Identifier-locator "
"addressing can be used to efficiently implement overlay networks for network "
"virtualization as well as solutions for use cases in mobility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:18
msgid ""
"ILA can be thought of as means to implement an overlay network without "
"encapsulation. This is accomplished by performing network address "
"translation on destination addresses as a packet traverses a network. To the "
"network, an ILA translated packet appears to be no different than any other "
"IPv6 packet. For instance, if the transport protocol is TCP then an ILA "
"translated packet looks like just another TCP/IPv6 packet. The advantage of "
"this is that ILA is transparent to the network so that optimizations in the "
"network, such as ECMP, RSS, GRO, GSO, etc., just work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:27
msgid ""
"The ILA protocol is described in Internet-Draft draft-herbert-intarea-ila."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:31
msgid "ILA terminology"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:33
msgid "Identifier"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:34
msgid ""
"A number that identifies an addressable node in the network independent of "
"its location. ILA identifiers are sixty-four bit values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:38
msgid "Locator"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:39
msgid ""
"A network prefix that routes to a physical host. Locators provide the "
"topological location of an addressed node. ILA locators are sixty-four bit "
"prefixes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:43
msgid "ILA mapping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:44
msgid ""
"A mapping of an ILA identifier to a locator (or to a locator and meta data). "
"An ILA domain maintains a database that contains mappings for all "
"destinations in the domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:48
msgid "SIR address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:49
msgid ""
"An IPv6 address composed of a SIR prefix (upper sixty- four bits) and an "
"identifier (lower sixty-four bits). SIR addresses are visible to "
"applications and provide a means for them to address nodes independent of "
"their location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:55
msgid "ILA address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:56
msgid ""
"An IPv6 address composed of a locator (upper sixty-four bits) and an "
"identifier (low order sixty-four bits). ILA addresses are never visible to "
"an application."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:60
msgid "ILA host"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:61
msgid ""
"An end host that is capable of performing ILA translations on transmit or "
"receive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:64
msgid "ILA router"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:65
msgid ""
"A network node that performs ILA translation and forwarding of translated "
"packets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:68
msgid "ILA forwarding cache"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:69
msgid ""
"A type of ILA router that only maintains a working set cache of mappings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:72
msgid "ILA node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/ila.rst:73
msgid ""
"A network node capable of performing ILA translations. This can be an ILA "
"router, ILA forwarding cache, or ILA host."
msgstr ""

